# Normalize line endings: all text files check out as LF on every platform,
# and are stored as LF in the repo regardless of each contributor's git config.
#
# Required for nightly rustfmt (`newline_style = "Unix"`, see .rustfmt.toml):
# the windows-latest rust-lint leg defaults to core.autocrlf=true and would
# otherwise check out source as CRLF, failing `cargo +nightly fmt --all --check`.
# `text=auto` still auto-detects binaries (images, etc.) and leaves them as-is.
* text=auto eol=lf
